Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Auditd rules not loading

Solution: Check syntax with sudo auditctl -l and verify file permissions
Ensure rules file is in /etc/audit/rules.d/ directory
Restart auditd service after changes
Issue: Scripts produce empty output files

Solution: Verify log files exist and are readable
Check script permissions (must be executable)
Ensure sufficient disk space in output directory
Run scripts with appropriate privileges (use sudo if needed)
Issue: Ausearch returns no results

Solution: Verify auditd is running: sudo systemctl status auditd
Check that audit rules are loaded: sudo auditctl -l
Generate some activity and wait 10-15 seconds for logging
Verify audit log exists: ls -la /var/log/audit/audit.log
